<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[264,1324,1676,1902]" box="[264,366,1676,1701]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis box="[264,366,1676,1701]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[264,1324,1676,1902]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
A widespread species, occurring from 
<collectingCountry box="[765,926,1716,1742]" name="Argentina" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">the Argentine</collectingCountry>
Neuquén Province in the north to the Chilean Magallanes Province in the south. The subgeneric assignment is not clear. 
<bibRefCitation author="Besch" box="[264,423,1796,1822]" pageId="13" pageNumber="22" refString="Besch, W. (1964) Systematik und Verbreitung der sudamerikanischen rheophilen Hydrachnellen. Beitrage zur Neotropischen Fauna, 3, 77 - 194." type="journal article" year="1964">
Besch (
<number box="[354,415,1796,1822]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1964.0">1964</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
assigned it to the typical subgenus. 
<bibRefCitation author="Cook" box="[863,1014,1796,1822]" pageId="13" pageNumber="22" refString="Cook, D. R. (1980) Studies on neotropical water mites. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 31, 1 - 645." type="journal article" year="1980">
Cook (
<number box="[945,1006,1796,1822]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1980.0">1980</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
placed it in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[264,440,1836,1861]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Corticacarides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[264,440,1836,1861]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Corticacarides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but later 
<bibRefCitation author="Cook" box="[566,718,1836,1862]" pageId="13" pageNumber="22" refString="Cook, D. R. (1988) Water mites from Chile. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 42, 1 - 356." type="journal article" year="1988">
Cook (
<number box="[648,709,1836,1862]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1988.0">1988</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
came to a different conclusion, and left it without subgeneric assignment.
</paragraph>
